               <birth when="1825"> He was born in <placeName ref="LOC1464Ankoba"/> in <date>1825</date>. </birth>
               
               
               <floruit notBefore="1845" notAfter="1908">He was a renowned Ethiopian scholar and theologian. 
                  He studied at various traditional schools in <placeName ref="LOC2393DabraW"/> , <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar"/> and 
                  <placeName ref="LOC1464Ankoba"/>. He was a follower of śost lǝdat. Since the situation of the followers of śost lǝdat deteriorated 
                  after the council of <placeName ref="LOC1980BoruMe"/> in <date>1878</date>,  he exiled
                  to <placeName ref="LOC4002Karan"/> where he taught Gǝʿǝz in the Catholic Mission. In <date>1887</date>, 
                  Kǝfla Giyorgis left <placeName ref="LOC4002Karan"/> for <placeName ref="wd:Q220"/> where 
                  he was invited to teach Gǝʿǝz at the Ethiopian college in <placeName ref="wd:Q237"/> where he had an opportunity to learn Latin and Italian, and he became an informant 
                  and consultant to <persName ref="PRS4876Guidi"/>. Having left <placeName ref="wd:Q220"/> in <date>1897</date>, he went to <placeName ref="LOC3957Jerusa"/>
                  where he encountered <persName ref="PRS5983KidanaW"/> who became his disciple.  During the elven years they spent, Kǝfla Giyorgis taught 
                  <persName ref="PRS5983KidanaW"/> sharing with him his vast theological knowledge. 
               </floruit>
               <death when="1908"> He died in <placeName ref="wd:Q1218"/> in <date>1908</date>. </death>
               
               
